We're delighted to announce the [Global Voices Citizen Media Summit
2010](https://summit2010.globalvoicesonline.org/)! Our gathering takes place
this year in Santiago, Chile on May 6-7, 2010.

Visit the [ Summit web site](https://summit2010.globalvoicesonline.org/) for
background information on [the goals of the
meeting](https://summit2010.globalvoicesonline.org/about/), the [program of
events](https://summit2010.globalvoicesonline.org/program/), [registration
details](https://summit2010.globalvoicesonline.org/about/register/) and
information about the vibrant city of Santiago. Among the highlights of the
proceedings will be the announcement of the winners of the [Breaking Borders
award](https://summit2010.globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/breaking-borders-
award/), a new prize created by Google and Global Voices to honor outstanding
web projects initiated by individuals or groups demonstrating courage, energy
and resourcefulness in using the Internet to promote freedom of expression.

![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/02/screenshot_iphone.jpg)

